Abiding by court deadlines is the most important practice in a court room. By abiding by a court deadline, one is able to display their upmost respect to the Honourable Judge, and allow for speedy proceedings for the benefit of all parties of the court. By not abiding by a court deadline, one is not able to display their respect, and hinders the proceedings, to the detriment of all parties. Court deadlines are set with a purpose, to activate a feasible but timely deadline, and failing to do so has damaged the integrity of this court, for which I truly apologise. In the future, I shall stride to never infringe upon a court deadline, as that would be to not take it seriously and mock all parties in the case, hence why never again shall I fail to abide by a court deadline.
